column4: <content>[verso] Bruegel in Spain: 1) Bosch motifs taken from Spanish Boschs-show detailed study of certain Bosch's particularly 'Hay Cart'; 2) Years until Large Landscape Series (1555) not accounted for. Th eseries not dated, but the preliminary drawing in the Louvre (T. 23) for Bosch N° 9 i sdated 1555. He may have been away all that time. (The earliest figure drawings (Fish, T. 44, & Ass in School, T. 45, dated 1556). This would explain why no earlier painting; [verso] Against Spain: 1) Th elong absence may be due to stay in Italy; 2) The Return journey led through Austria & Germany; 3) Van Mander does not mention stay in Spain; 4) No Spanish landscapes by Bruegel? [doorstreept]; 5) The main pictures of importance  for Bruegel were 1) Last Judgment [onleesbaar], lost); 2) Epiphany, Prado; 3) Vienna Last Judgment (4) Hay Cart. Of these Prado Epiphany was confiscated by Philip II from Jean de Casembrot (when & where?) and there exist many copies and Hay Cart there was a version in Arundel Coll. [onleesbaar] Jeronimo Bos (p. 285)</content>
